Recently, I realized that somewhere along the way, I lost that fire I had here. I got caught up in this being my job that I stopped enjoying this as a creative outlet. 
This year has been a pretty hard year for me, and I stepped back a bit lately so I could take care of things with me and my family. 
Giving that time to think, I realize that I miss the modeling part and creating fun photo art a lot. 
Needless to say, I am now eager to get back to that...thinking of fun photoshoots, cosplays, and creative outfits. Also seeing the reactions to my posts this week, it made me realize that the things that make me unique are also the reasons why you all follow me. So I wanna get back to showing off that uniqueness!
If you have ideas for things you want to see me try or need outfit inspo, feel free to let me know in the comments or DM me! I love hearing your ideas! Hope you all have a fabulous weekend!

If you know me, you know I am all about the accessories! So for this look breakdown, here is what I did to make the entire look POP!

I found this amazing dress at @thecurvevault . I don't know if they still carry this one, but if not, there are plenty of cute things there. 
I wanted to accentuate the waist, so I used this belt by @torrid. Torrid has some super cute belts for dresses and rompers. I love their corset belts best. 
As for the tights...everyone asks me about these tights all the time! They are from @target ! They wear super well and I love to put them with dresses and even shorts.
The chunky jewelry is actually all one piece and is from @lanebryant ! Chunky jewelry is awesome because it gives this real put together look, even if you are feeling a bit like a hot mess.
To finish up, I am wearing my favorite pair of @drmartensofficial because I am all about living my best 90s life, and they are super comfy!
What is your must have accessory?
Also make sure you are following because I am going to be doing outfit breakdowns every week and if you have suggestions for things you need ideas for how to wear, please be sure to dm me!

Having one of those days where you are tummy conscious? Then I have a fresh look for you!

I am absolutely loving the empire waist sheer, long length top that is starting to trend! I picked mine up at @thecurvevault in black. 

Why this works: You can wear this over a bodycon dress or a Maxi Dress of similar length. You can also wear with shorts or jeans! It is so versatile. With the empire waist, it emphasizes your waist, rather than your tummy. Plus it is so cute that it will give the extra boost in confidence too!

I paired mine with a @torrid Maxi Dress and sandals, also from Torrid. I am looking forward to wearing this with denim when it starts to cool down too!

I know that this style breakdown is a little different from my usual style ideas because I am actually talking about hiding a certain part of your body. Here is why though: I want people to love themselves, and sometimes we have days where that is a little harder than others. I have a few style follow ups in the works for those days. 

I hope you like this look! What would you wear with this?

When you don't get to see @taylorswift live but still want the experience for the Eras Film! 
This was my Eras film look! I had so much fun putting this together and managed to stay thrifty with coupons and thrift shopping...so here is the breakdown:
*Denim Moto Jacket by @loft (I used a 50% coupon from an online sale and stacked my rewards to snag this baby)
•HiLo dress was found on clearance at @rue21 ! They always have cute festival and concert wear!
•Tights were from @target ! Their Fishnets last me forever, and the sequin ones were just too cute.
• Boots were thrifted from @lovethycurvesboutique . I always find the cutest stuff there!
•Hat was from @amazonstylestore ! I get most of my hats there these days. Will include in my stories/highlights.  It was my only real Amazon days purchase!

My total cost was under $75, and I can use it all for other things! I loved my look and had so much fun!

Did you see the Eras Film? If so, tag me in your look post so I can see it!
